{"questionId":"3302361","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following guide is used by the coach to determine the strength of the correlation between the ranks for long jump and high jump.</p>\n<table style=\"width:359px;height:158px;border-color:#000000;margin-left:150px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"bold\"><mo stretchy=\"true\">|</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"true\">|</mo></mstyle></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Strength</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>000</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>199</mn></math>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;\">&nbsp; Very weak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>200</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>399</mn></math>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;\">&nbsp; Weak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>400</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>599</mn></math>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;\">&nbsp; Moderate</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>600</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>799</mn></math>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;\">&nbsp; Strong</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:167.683px;text-align:center;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>800</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>000</mn></math>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:173.317px;\">&nbsp; Very strong</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"padding-left:150px;\">&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the strength of the correlation between the rankings as indicated by the table and interpret this in the context of the question.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>moderate (correlation)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>as long jump ranking increases, high jump ranking will (likely) increase&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3302361","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.1c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the strength of the correlation between the rankings as indicated by the table and interpret this in the context of the question.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.10—Spearman’s rank correlation coefficient"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}